Up for sale is an AR 15 rifle I recently built. I function checked the firearm with 44 rounds of 5.56, which is all the shooting this AR has seen. There were no issues with the rifle during testing. The sale price includes the rifle, the optic, all the accessories shown, and the brass.

It also includes an airsoft clone of the LMT SOPMOD stock, which fits on the milspec tube with very little wobble. There is also a standard sling and an extra trigger guard in the package.

It comes with 6 Teflon coated D&H 30 round magazines. The rifle has a Magpul Back-Up Sight. The optic is a Vortex Strikefire red/green dot sight, which comes with a 2x magnifier and a 1/3 cowitness mount. I have 36 rounds of brass cased 5.56 to go with the gun.

I am also adding in about 7 pounds of once-fired brass (mostly .223, a few others mixed in though) for whoever buys the package.

If you're interested, you can message me anytime. I'm willing to listen to any reasonable offer, though cash is preferred. Thanks for reading!

A non-lead projectile with a Hollow Point Flat Based (HPFB) design. It's OAL is 0.955” allowing it to function properly even though it is a hollow point. This is a very beautiful and Mint condition Early 1955 Springfield Armory CMP Correct Grade M1 Garand Post War rifle with the Original CMP Correct Grade paperwork. It is in the desirable 5.7 million serial number range. Only 6152 rifles were produced in this serial number range.
99% overall finish that is all matching and flat mint. It is the very pleasant USGI Dark Charcoal finish. Barrel ME is a 1.0 and the TE is 1.5 and the barrel still shows the cutting marks in the muzzle and bore. Chamber is "in the White", showing it is original finish. Bore is mirror bright and looks new. This rifle looks unissued. All the wood, stock and handguards, are Mint and match beautifully, showing very few of the normal handling marks. Stock locks up tightly and shows very few of the usual dings or handling marks. The Stock shows the ½” DAS cartouche and Proof P with Sarifs which are the indicative of Springfield Armory acceptance. The Wood shows beautiful walnut grain and is still “in the grease”.

Receiver has drawing number F 6528291 with a heat lot of A 5 3.

Trigger housing drawing number 6528290-SA.

NHC Elevation Knob and DRC Windage knob.
o Gas cylinder lock screw.

title: For Sale:  Colt LE901 -16S 901 .308 Carbine w/ Conversion Kit
postcontent: Colt LE901-16S™ is the rifle for the hunt. At first glance you would think that the Colt 901 is just a .308 Win./7.62 NATO version of a standard AR-15, much like any other .308 AR out there, but it is a lot more than that. The Colt LE901-16S is a “Modular Carbine,” which means it can be adapted to any AR-15 platform upper. This isn’t a new concept, because there are of course a whole bunch of different caliber uppers for ARs. The difference is in all the other ones, they have adapted a standard size AR magazine to boutique calibers and cartridge designs. The Colt 901 is different. It can be adapted from .308/7.62, using standard P-Mags, to .223/5.56, using standard AR mags, and back again, in literally seconds. The design uses one proprietary part, and you have to swap out the recoil system. It is that simple, and it works fantastic.

title: For Sale:  Ladies only Concealed Carry Handgun Certification Class
location: Moore County Wildlife Conservation Club, Fayetteville, North Carolina
postcontent:
Hey Guys, 

Welcome to our Ladies Only Concealed Carry Handgun Certification Class!! My wife Kim and I will host it at our normal location at the Moore County Wildlife Conservation Club at 1820 Camp Easter Rd, in Carthage. 

We do our best to create an environment where everyone feels safe and everyone feels comfortable taking this class. It is important to know that I teach this class to the lowest common denominator. Most classes, the majority of the people have never fired a weapon or have very little experience. That is great. We will teach the class so that you are very comfortable if that is the case, so do not feel pressure that you need to have experience or knowledge coming into the class.

My goals in the class are simple:

•	For the class to be very safe and free from any injury
•	For you to learn something you didn't know, regardless of your skill level
•	For everyone to be treated with respect
•	For you to get your certification of completion so you can exercise your 2nd Amendment rights and be better protected wherever you go
Here is my list of needs and items that need your attention:

•	The class will start at 8:00am sharp with 100% attendance required. I ask that you arrive at 7:45-7:50 a.m. so we start on time.
•	You will need the following items for the class:

•	MANDATORY
o	gun (if semi-auto, please have at least two magazines; if revolver, please have at least one speed loaders)
	If you do not have gun, ammo, hearing and eye protection, we can provide them
o	50 rounds of ammunition
o	Holster
o	eye and ear protection
o	billed cap
•	RECOMMENDED
o	long pants 
o	bug spray 
o	sunscreen 
•	Other Facts
o	We will provide training, targets, and teaching
o	We will be providing lunch, so we can have a working lunch, as well as we will provide water for the range. If you want something other than water, you should bring it. You are welcome to keep it in our cooler. 
o	The class is $85, which includes the above lunch and drinks. Gun/ammo/eye and ear protection is extra.
o	Payment is due 8 days before the class.  We accept paypal/check/cash/visa.
o	The class is scheduled from 8am-6pm. Be prepared to stay that long, though we may get out a bit early
o	Attendance: YOU ARE REQUIRED to confirm with us if you are going to be there.  So, please email my below email and let me know for sure if you are going to be in the class. 
	OR if you have signed up, but you are not going to attend, we need to know that as well. Your slot may be able to be filled by another.
	If you have paid and you can refill your slot, we will give you a refund. If you don’t show up, it is non-refundable. If we are full and you give us notice of cancellation, but we can refill it, we will give you a refund.
•	Rules – Safety and Respect – if you don’t have either of these two requirements, you will be ejected from the class. We have fun in my classes in a safe and respectful way.

If you have any questions or needs that are specific to you, please let us know as soon as possible. We will do our best to answer your questions or help with whatever need(s) you have. Please do not be afraid to ask questions or raise concerns. We are going to be handling and firing handguns. That is really fun if done safely. However, if there is any issue, whether it is a physical impediment or anxiety issue that you have, we need to know that. Please know that anxiety from someone who has little or no experience with weapons is very normal and we appreciate knowing as we can help you with that.  We will assist you any way we can, including more individual attention if needed, for your safety and success.

Guys, thank you all so much! We look forward to seeing you all out there for a safe and fun day! 

Thank you!

Buck & Kimberly Mims
REDACTED
REDACTED
